<h2 id="Syntax">Syntax</h2>
<pre class="twopartsyntaxbox"><a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/Value_definition_syntax" title="CSS/Value_definition_syntax">Formal syntax</a>: <code>none <a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#Single_bar" title="Single bar: the two entities are optional, but exactly one must be present.">|</a> [ weight <a href="/en-US/docs/CSS/Value_definition_syntax#Double_bar" title="Double bar: the two entities are optional, and may appear in any order.">||</a> style ]</code></pre>
<pre>font-synthesis: none
font-synthesis: weight
font-synthesis: style
font-synthesis: weight style

font-synthesis: initial
font-synthesis: inherit
font-synthesis: unset
</pre>
<h3 id="Values">Values</h3>
<dl><dt>
  <code>none</code></dt>
 <dd>
  This keyword indicates that neither bold nor italic typeface must be synthesized.</dd>
 <dt>
  <code>weight</code></dt>
 <dd>
  This keyword indicates that a bold typeface may be synthesized if needed.</dd>
 <dt>
  <code>style</code></dt>
 <dd>
  This keyword indicates that an italic typeface may be synthesized if needed.</dd>
</dl>